p out the door of her apartment while the Gestapo's attention was momentarily diverted, and make it to her husband, Herbert in Berlin. The Strausses, together, spent the next six months hiding in Germany, planning for their escape, and continuing to evade the Gestapo by just seconds. In May, 1943, they managed to slip across the Swiss border.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Historical.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000z978311074329640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082329635440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823296354423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823296354/original  a978-3-11-074329-6  Fordham University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK